T}@T{
T}
.TE
.PP
When an exception is thrown, you can retrieve the error message through
getLastErrMsg() or getLastError() to get the error code.
For more error handling, you can refer to the Common Error Handling Guide.
.SH VERSION
.PP
v5.10 and above
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
Set character set for the client to GB18030.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
> db.setClientCharset("GB18030")
\f[]
.fi
